Overview

This file examines the microbiome profile of triplicate samples and generates the figures presented in Figure 1. Reproducibility of the synthetic long read sequencing for pediatric urine samples.

Set-up

Library libraries, workspace

library(here)
library(ggplot2)
library(dplyr)
library(phyloseq)
library(speedyseq)
library(microshades)
library(cowplot)


load(here("data", "cairibu_data_blca.RData"))

Plot replicates

Create and print a subset of microshades plots

# Define phyla names
exp_phylum_blca <- c('Proteobacteria', 'Actinobacteria', 'Bacteroidetes', 'Firmicutes')

color_dfs_blca <- create_color_dfs(subset_blca, group_level = "phylum",subgroup_level = "species", selected_groups = exp_phylum_blca)

new_legend <- custom_legend(color_dfs_blca$mdf, color_dfs_blca$cdf, group_level = "phylum",subgroup_level = "species")

# Subset to representative samples

mdf_blca_sub <- color_dfs_blca$mdf %>% filter(place %in% c("A4", "C3", "D5", "H2"))

plot_blca <- plot_microshades(mdf_blca_sub,color_dfs_blca$cdf, x= "plate") + 
  #ggtitle("BLCA") + 
  theme(legend.text=element_text(size=16))  + 
  facet_wrap(~place, nrow = 1)+
  xlab("Sample") +
  theme(legend.position = "none") +
  theme(axis.text.x = element_text(angle = 0))

# Plot Figure 1A
plot_grid(plot_blca, new_legend, rel_heights = c(1, .4), nrow=1)

Summarize abundance of specific species across replicates

replicates <- subset_blca %>% select(place, Sample, Abundance, plate,phylum, species) %>%
  filter(species %in% color_dfs_blca$mdf$Top_species) 

replicate_summary <- replicates %>% group_by(place, species) %>%
  summarize(minimum = min(Abundance*100), maximum = max(Abundance*100), average = mean(Abundance*100), stdev = sd(Abundance*100), covar = sd(Abundance)/mean(Abundance) )

# Plot Figure 1B

plot_select_rep <- replicate_summary %>% filter(species %in% c("Anaerococcus lactolyticus", "Finegoldia magna", "Peptoniphilus harei")) %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = place, y = average)) + 
  geom_point(size = .5) +
  ylim(c(0,100)) +
  ylab("Relative Abundance") +
  xlab("Sample") +
  theme(axis.text = element_text(size=7)) +
  geom_errorbar(aes(ymin = average - stdev, ymax = average + stdev)) +
  facet_wrap(~species) 

plot_select_rep
